Buffalo  City Metro is warning motorists to pay their traffic fines or “face the full might of the law”. Spokesman Samkelo Ngwenya said: “This afternoon [Wednesday] the BCM traffic and law enforcement services conducted a roadblock on the N2 between East London and King William’s Town. Statistics received reveal that that a total amount of R44000 was paid on the spot and 165 notices issued. –  “For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions”.